      >
      <tr
        ><td>gpt-4o-mini</td><td><strong>$0.0003</strong></td><td><strong>$0.0001</strong></td><td
          >1,953</td
        ><td>109</td></tr
      >
      <tr
        ><td>gpt-5.4-nano</td><td><strong>$0.0003</strong></td><td><strong>$0.0002</strong></td><td
          >1,080</td
        ><td>40</td></tr
      >
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>So yield is ($0.004/day * 365 days) / $1 = 146%.</p>
  <p>
    Remember GitHub Copilot's monthly premium requests? Or CrofAI's daily request plans? Per request
    billing isn't sustainable. And Jatevo is a vibe coded website leaking too many implementation
    details, with no $65 mil series A or rich founder to bear the load. I'm bearish.
  </p>

  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <p>If you pay as you go:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>$20/mo or $100/mo GPT → ~39x multiplier</li>
    <li>$200/mo GPT → ~78x multiplier</li>
    <li>Surplus Intelligence → up to 100x multiplier</li>
  </ul>
  <p>If you invest in crypto, and 1 year later things go well:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      $1300 DIEM, AI use → got $ from DIEM appreciating AND got $365 in AI (would cost $260-$1.83 on
      Surplus Intelligence)
    </li>
    <li>$1300 DIEM, reselling → got $ from DIEM appreciating AND got $182.5</li>
    <li>
      ${dollars(190 * morPrice)} MOR, AI use → got $ from MOR appreciating AND got $85 from MOR interest
      AND got $365 in AI (would cost $260-$1.83 on Surplus Intelligence)
    </li>
    <li>
      ${dollars(190 * morPrice)} MOR, reselling → got $ from MOR appreciating AND got $85 from MOR interest
      AND got $182.5
    </li>
    <li>
      $100 JTVO, AI use → got $ from JTVO appreciating AND got 36.5k GPT requests (could cost
      anything on Surplus Intelligence, realistically between $3.65 and $365)
    </li>
    <li>$100 JTVO, reselling → got $ from JTVO appreciating AND got $146</li>
  </ul>
  <p>If you invest in crypto, and 1 year later things go awry:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>$1300 DIEM → Venice shuts down, you only ever made $182.5, you lost $1117.5 (86%)</li>
    <li>
      ${dollars(190 * morPrice)} MOR → MORDIEM shuts down hard, you only ever made $182.5, you lost ${
        dollars(190 * morPrice - 182.5)
      }
      ({Math.round(((190 * morPrice - 182.5) / (190 * morPrice)) * 100)}%)
    </li>
    <li>$100 JTVO → Jatevo shuts down, you made $146</li>
  </ul>
</BlogPost>
